item.title: Zero(WIP) added wire
item.dc:creator: @poopler40 poopler40
item.description:
@poopler40 wrote:

amy_webb:

I was wondering if it was made for a specific occupation so i could base it off of that, all i can really say is that the colouring on the cream arm pads is a little bland, may add some shading to it. Also, the squares look messy, but i believe you may be doing that to give it that rs look because a lot of their models are messy when it comes to those details. Other then that there really isn’t much you can do, i expect your wireframe is extremely clean, but maybe the shades on the vest, bring them closer together or make it darker because the top where i’m assuming the light should be looks a little too light for it.

i can let you give a go at it. the squares are aligned in meta but in but datmaker distorts them for the outcome you see
